ull,"primary_group_flair_url":null,"primary_group_flair_bg_color":null,"primary_group_flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":48,"hidden":false,"trust_level":3,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":63862,"name":"Kyle Nitzsche","username":"kyleN","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/forum.snapcraft.io/kylen/{size}/229_2.png","created_at":"2020-02-27T14:28:46.754Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI think \u003ccode\u003esnap interface serial-port\u003c/code\u003e lists the \u003cstrong\u003esnaps\u003c/strong\u003e that provide slots and the snaps the have plugs for the named interface (in this case serial-port interface). That is, it does not seem list see “serial port \u003cstrong\u003edevices\u003c/strong\u003e” as the current text indicates. For example, I have a gadget named ‘my-test-gadg’ that declares the slot, and I have a snap ‘my-sp-app’ that has the plug, and I see this:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003eknitzsche@localhost:~$ snap interface serial-port\nname:    serial-port\nsummary: allows accessing a specific serial port\nplugs:\n  - my-sp-app\nslots:\n  - my-test-gadg\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-02-27T14:28:46.754Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":9,"reads":48,"readers_count":47,"score":54.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":7913,"topic_slug":"the-serial-port-interface","display_username":"Kyle Nitzsche","primary_group_name":null,"primary_group_flair_url":null,"primary_group_flair_bg_color":null,"primary_group_flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":52,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":63866,"name":"Kyle Nitzsche","username":"kyleN","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/forum.snapcraft.io/kylen/{size}/229_2.png","created_at":"2020-02-27T15:51:06.450Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI just found that declaring a usb-vendor or usb-product with a four-digit INT with a leading 0 causes a toolchain failure leading to a snap that cannot be uploaded, that is, these fail:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003eslots:\n  serial-port:\n    usb-vendor: 0658\n    usb-product: 0200\n    ....\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-02-27T15:52:09.718Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":6,"reads":45,"readers_count":44,"score":44.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":7913,"topic_slug":"the-serial-port-interface","display_username":"Kyle Nitzsche","primary_group_name":null,"primary_group_flair_url":null,"primary_group_flair_bg_color":null,"primary_group_flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":52,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":63885,"name":"Jamie Strandboge","username":"jdstrand","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/forum.snapcraft.io/jdstrand/{size}/6376_2.png","created_at":"2020-02-27T18:41:31.367Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-username=\"kyleN\" data-post=\"5\" data-topic=\"7913\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://forum.snapcraft.io/user_avatar/forum.snapcraft.io/kylen/40/229_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e kyleN:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eslots: serial-port: usb-vendor: 0658 usb-product: 0200 …\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eUse this instead:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003eslots:\n  serial-port:\n    usb-vendor: 0x0658\n    usb-product: 0x0200\n    ....\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-02-27T18:41:31.367Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":6,"reads":42,"readers_count":41,"score":38.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":7913,"topic_slug":"the-serial-port-interface","display_username":"Jamie Strandboge","primary_group_name":null,"primary_group_flair_url":null,"primary_group_flair_bg_color":null,"primary_group_flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":21,"hidden":false,"trust_level":3,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":63910,"name":"Kyle Nitzsche","username":"kyleN","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/forum.snapcraft.io/kylen/{size}/229_2.png","created_at":"2020-02-28T00:18:16.593Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI cannot yet build a gadget that declares the serial-port slot and declares BOTH the path and the two usb-* attributes.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003eslots:\n  serial-port:\n    path: /dev/ttyACM0\n    usb-vendor: 0x0658\n    usb-product: 0x0200 \n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eResults in this:\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ccode\u003esnap \"my-gadge\" has bad plugs or slots: serial-port (serial-port path attribute specifies invalid symlink location)\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-02-28T00:20:23.225Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":22,"reads":40,"readers_count":39,"score":123.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":7913,"topic_slug":"the-serial-port-interface","display_username":"Kyle Nitzsche","primary_group_name":null,"primary_group_flair_url":null,"primary_group_flair_bg_color":null,"primary_group_flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":52,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":63943,"name":"Jamie Strandboge","username":"jdstrand","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/forum.snapcraft.io/jdstrand/{size}/6376_2.png","created_at":"2020-02-28T13:17:35.970Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThis is discussed up above, with usb-vendor and usb-product, ‘path’ specifies the symlink name: \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/snapcore/snapd/blob/master/interfaces/builtin/serial_port.go#L77\"\u003ehttps://github.com/snapcore/snapd/blob/master/interfaces/builtin/serial_port.go#L77\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eUse this:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003eslots:\n  serial-port:\n    path: /dev/serial-port-?\n    usb-vendor: 0x0658\n    usb-product: 0x0200 \n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-02-28T13:17:35.970Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":7,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":4,"reads":40,"readers_count":39,"score